<TITLE> Beware of misinterpreters: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has urged the ulemas, or Muslim scholars, to be alert to the danger of people being misled through misinterpretation of religion. "You have to be alert so that none can mislead the people through misinterpretation of Islam," she told them while inaugurating the extended part of Baitul Mukarram National Mosque on Friday morning. The prime minister said Islam is the religion of peace. "You have to highlight the main messages of the religion to the people." The Tk 260 million (26 crore) project, financed by Saudi Arabian government, is being implemented for its beautification and expansion of facilities for female devotees. Mentioning her government's eagerness to develop the country' mosques, numbering around 3 lakh, Hasina said they wanted to make the mosques the centre of welfare activities. She emphasised expansion of mosque-based library activities and listed measures taken by 1971-75 Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's government for promotion of Islam, including the establishment of Islamic Foundation. State minister for religions affairs Shahjahan Mia, deputy finance minister of Saudi Arabia Mohammed bin Saleh al Gifail, religious affairs secretary Abdul Rab Howlader and officials of Islamic Foundation were present. b
